Say hello to Kelsey, our Featured Citizen of the Week!<br><br><b>Kelsey </b>moved to town all the way back on June 19th, 2006. Living here for more than two years makes her a regular Millsberry veteran. <br><br>Kelsey enjoys the scenic vistas from her <a href="http://millsberry.com/home/?user=wezel11"><a href='/home/?user=wezel11'>14299 Wren Lane</a></a> home. And no one blames her for not wanting to give up the cool breezes of her beloved Lakeview neighborhood. <br><br>The lake is frozen this time of year, which makes it perfect for ice-skating. In Kelsey's case, she may prefer a game of hockey. With a trophy from Slap Shot Shootout, there's no doubt she can hold her own.  <br><br>Actually, Kelsey has plenty of gold to go around. She's collected a total of 20 trophies, ranging from Peabody Park Cleanup to Sudoku. Being a self-described athlete, it should come as no surprise that Kelsey holds top prizes for Tricky Touchdown, Sink Three, and Home Run Derby, too. <br><br>And she certainly doesn't have a problem exercising her legs. Kelsey's interest in soccer probably helped her prepare for Laslo Balint's Walk for Malawi. It's a good bet that after running up and down a soccer field, walking for a great cause is no sweat.<br><br>Some of Kelsey's other interests include acting and reading. For her, memorizing lines from a script must be a breeze! <br><br>When Kelsey isn't acting her heart out, she's likely relaxing to her favorite tunes. Her favorite music includes Country, Country, and more Country. Hey, there's nothing wrong with knowing what you like. <br><br>If you happen to run into Kelsey, be sure to give her a high-five and thank her for being such a great citizen!<br></div>
